HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 799
By Crawford
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Helen Scott on being
named Bristolian of the Year by the Bristol
Herald Courier.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Helen Scott, who was recently named Bristolian of
the Year by the Bristol Herald Courier; and
WHEREAS, this recognition pays tribute to Ms. Scott and her more than two decades of
faithful service, community collaboration, and ongoing commitment to ensuring the availability of
quality health care to all residents of the region; and
WHEREAS, Helen Scott is the Executive Director at Healing Hands Health Center and
has served with the program since October 2003; and
WHEREAS, while Ms. Scott adroitly leads the organization, she modestly asserts that
this honor belongs to the incredible staff, volunteers, students, partners, and supporters who
make Healing Hands Health possible; and
WHEREAS, Helen Scott's remarkable tenure with Healing Hands Health speaks
volumes about her commitment to making the region a better place for everyone, particularly
those who are most in need of health care; and
WHEREAS, her dedication to public service is a testament to the impact one person can
have on a community; Ms. Scott has left an indelible mark on Bristol by acting on her steadfast
belief in the power of giving back; and
WHEREAS, as the region continues to grow and evolve, the foundation that Helen Scott
has helped build will remain a guiding light for future generations; and
HJR0799
010870
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Helen Scott is most worthy of our approbation on this special occasion;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Helen Scott on being named Bristolian of the
Year by the Bristol Herald Courier, commend her exemplary service as Executive Director at
Healing Hands Health Center, and praise her unwavering commitment to making quality health
care readily available to the residents of Bristol and the region.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
